{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC25","title":"Wake up to the AlarmKit API"},"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Rrrr-rrrrr-innng! From countdown timers in your recipe app to wake-up alarms in your travel planning app, the AlarmKit framework in iOS and iPadOS 26 brings timers and alarms to the Lock Screen, Dynamic Island, and more. Learn how to create and manage your app’s alarms, customize their Live Activities, and offer custom alert actions using the App Intents framework. To get the most from this video, we recommend first watching “Meet ActivityKit” from WWDC23."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-230-wake-up-to-the-alarmkit-api"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alarm is a permanent alert for pre-determined timely alerts, based on schedule or countdown"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Breaks through silent mode and focus, therefore users have to consent a permission dialog","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Constists of: Title, app name, stop button, optional snooze button – alternatively custom button","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Alarms also supported in Standby and on Apple Watch","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Custom countdown interface using live activities supported, too (lock screen, dynamic island, standby)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-230-Custom-Button","type":"image"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Authorization","level":2,"text":"Authorization"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Request authorization manually via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmManager"},{"type":"text","text":" or automatically (upon creating first alarm)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users can change authorization in Settings app anytime"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSAlarmKitUsageDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" to your Info.plist"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Check state via "},{"code":"AlarmManager.shared.authorizationState","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" like here:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import AlarmKit","","func checkAuthorization() {","","  switch AlarmManager.shared.authorizationState {","    case .notDetermined:","      \/\/ Manually request authorization","    case .authorized:","      \/\/ Proceed with scheduling","    case .denied:","      \/\/ Inform status is not authorized","  }","  ","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Creation","level":2,"text":"Creation"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Countdown-duration","level":3,"text":"Countdown duration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can specify a countdown duration for before and after the alert:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-230-Countdown-duration"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set it like this:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import AlarmKit","","func scheduleAlarm() {","  \/* ... *\/","  let countdownDuration = Alarm.CountdownDuration(preAlert: (10 * 60), postAlert: (5 * 60))","  \/* ... *\/","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Schedule","level":3,"text":"Schedule"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Schedules can be fixed or relative"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A fixed schedule alarm is set to an absolute specific date that doesn’t react to timezone changes"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use a relative schedule to account for timezone changes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tabNavigator","tabs":[{"title":"Fixed schedule","content":[{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import AlarmKit","","func scheduleAlarm() {","  \/* ... *\/","  let keynoteDateComponents = DateComponents(","    calendar: .current,","    year: 2025,","    month: 6,","    day: 9,","    hour: 9,","    minute: 41)","  let keynoteDate = Calendar.current.date(from: keynoteDateComponents)!","  let scheduleFixed = Alarm.Schedule.fixed(keynoteDate)","  \/* ... *\/","}"]}]},{"title":"Relative schedule","content":[{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import AlarmKit","","func scheduleAlarm() {","  \/* ... *\/¥","  let time = Alarm.Schedule.Relative.Time(hour: 7, minute: 0)","  let recurrence = Alarm.Schedule.Relative.Recurrence.weekly([","    .monday,","    .wednesday,","    .friday","  ])","  ","  let schedule = Alarm.Schedule.Relative(time: time, repeats: recurrence)","  \/* ... *\/","}"]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Appearance","level":3,"text":"Appearance"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which takes ","type":"text"},{"code":"text","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"textColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"code":"systemImageName","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (symbol used in dynamic island)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmPresentation.Alert"},{"type":"text","text":" which takes "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"title"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stopButton"},{"type":"text","text":" (the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmButton"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Extra rendering information provided via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmAttributes"},{"type":"text","text":", containing the alarm presentation, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tintColor"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Put everything into an ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmConfiguraton","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which takes ","type":"text"},{"code":"countdownDuration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"attributes","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Actions","level":3,"text":"Actions"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can create another "},{"code":"AlarmButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" such as for Snooze\/Repeat etc."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pass it to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmPresentation.Alert"},{"text":" initializer via ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secondaryButton"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secondaryButtonBehavior"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can pass "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".countdown"},{"type":"text","text":" to the latter parameter, or a custom behavior"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use countdown functionality, you’re required to provide a live activity for it"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn more: "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10184-Meet-ActivityKit","isActive":true}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Code sample:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import AlarmKit","import ActivityKit","import WidgetKit","","struct AlarmLiveActivity: Widget {","  var body: some WidgetConfiguration {","    ActivityConfiguration(for: AlarmAttributes<CookingData>.self) { context in","      switch context.state.mode {","      case .countdown:","        countdownView(context)","      case .paused:","        pausedView(context)","      case .alert:","        alertView(context)","      }","    } dynamicIsland: { context in ","      DynamicIsland {","        DynamicIslandExpandedRegion(.leading) {","          leadingView(context)","        }","        DynamicIslandExpandedRegion(.trailing) {","          trailingView(context)","        }","      } compactLeading: {","        compactLeadingView(context)","      } compactTrailing: {","        compactTrailingView(context)","      } minimal: {","        minimalView(context)","      }","    }","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Conform a struct to the "},{"code":"AlarmMetadata","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol to pass custom metadata to the context attributes"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is how you can add extra UI to give context about your alarm (such as “Fry􁐅”)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Sometimes (like until device is unlocked upon restart) live activity will not be available","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlarmPresentation.Paused","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for a paused state in system alarm UI, add to attributes","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tint color is used to associate your alarm to your app, passed as part of attributes"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For custom buttons, you need to specify an (open) app intent like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["public struct OpenInApp: LiveActivityIntent {","    public func perform() async throws -> some IntentResult { .result() }","    ","    public static var title: LocalizedStringResource = \"Open App\"","    public static var description = IntentDescription(\"Opens the Sample app\")","    public static var openAppWhenRun = true","    ","    @Parameter(title: \"alarmID\")","    public var alarmID: String","    ","    public init(alarmID: String) {","        self.alarmID = alarmID","    }","    ","    public init() {","        self.alarmID = \"\"","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Sound","level":3,"text":"Sound"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Default system sounds useds if nothing specified, providing custom sound is possible","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Define custom sound by using ","type":"text"},{"code":"AlertConfiguration.AlertSound.named","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"File must be in apps main bundle or library sounds folder in app container"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Pass it to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sound"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmConfiguration"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Lifecycle","level":2,"text":"Lifecycle"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Schedule an alarm using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmManager.shared.schedule"},{"type":"text","text":" with an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"configuration"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can adjust the countdown, or cancel, stop, pause, and resume it programmatically"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Best to use for things like a cooking timer or wake up alarm"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Not a replacement for critical alerts or time-sensitive notifications"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Make sure to keep things clear, in your button titles and in your live activity","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Author note: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":" is only available on iOS, iPadOS, and Mac Catalyst"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Written-By","level":2,"text":"Written By"},{"type":"row","columns":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"Jeehut"}]}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Cihat Gündüz","anchor":"Cihat-G%C3%BCnd%C3%BCz"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/Jeehut","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Jeehut","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/x.com\/Jeehut","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/fline.dev","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}],"size":4}],"numberOfColumns":5},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Missing anything? Corrections? "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/c